Now, a level 57 mage probably isn't going to summon a focused GV Earth pet if he has the epic pet to choose from, but he will still have the flexibility and option to do so (IE: Mob rips through epic in less than 5 minutes, can't resummon epic, etc).   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etadanikm>EtadanikM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/02 8:50:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7761.topic&index=70>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Concerning the necro epic...</span><hr size=1> Necros don't ask for the same thing as druids because, unlike druids, we like the snare effect on our epic since we don't get anything at &lt; level 10, or for that matter, &lt; level 63 that matches it.  The alternative to not using the necro epic is to use dooming darkness to snare, and that's a level 30ish spell.  Considering that the epic is mana-free, people prefer casting that every 1.5 mins or so than having to mem and cast a level 30ish spell in order to get mobs snared for the same amount of time.  The key is that necro epic snare &gt; level 30ish snare, for the most part.<br>
<br>
Druids are different.  They get ensnare, which lasts like 10 minutes, and is MUCH more preferrable to their epic snare, which lasts a mere 3.  Since druids don't have that many DoTs to start with, making their epic stackable with their snare makes it a great boon to them soloing, grouping, and raiding.  <br>
<br>
Now if you said change the necro epic so at level 63 it loses its snare and becomes pure damage, than yes, it would be something the necro community might indeed ask for.  But that's a bit too much, methinks.  Let the epic go, and look forward to new and brighter things.<br>
