<br>
Beastlord mainhand epic remains useful for the proc (same as earthcaller) until they get a better slow, which I think is never. There is a level 60 40% slow, but it's really rare, and the proc goes up to 50%.<br>
<br>
Rogue epic remains useful until they get a 41% haste item, 150 points of aura of battle and vengeance items, primal offhander, and a good main hand. For the lazier, it's useful until they get 41% haste, primal and a NTOV/high end luclin main hand.<br>
<br>
Ranger and beastlord offhands are same as rogue epic (except 13/21 and 13/22 instead of 15/25). Most are willing to drop them when they get 41% haste and a good offhander though, since they don't benefit as much from the +ATK.<br>
<br>
Bard epic cannot yet be bagged, but drops we're seeing in POP suggests that it will be possible to dump it once you have the right set of POP loot. (i.e. the ring that's a stringed instrument)<br>
<br>
Warrior, paladin and shadowknight epics are generally considered not worth doing.<br>
<br>
The three priest epics remain useful always.<br>
<br>
I don't think (but don't know for sure) that there is anything that will replace wizard epic in game.<br>
<br>
Necro: dunno<br>
Enchanter: mostly junk it seems<br>
